article.description: Marshall Moses scored 17 points to lead four double-figure scorers for Oklahoma State in an 86-73 season-opening win over Houston Baptist on Saturday.
article.headline: Oklahoma State rides balanced attack to season-opening win
article.linkText: Oklahoma State tops Houston Baptist in opener
article.story: STILLWATER, Okla. -- Marshall Moses scored 17 points to lead four double-figure scorers for Oklahoma State in an 86-73 season-opening win over Houston Baptist on Saturday. The Cowboys also got 16 points from freshman Jean-Paul Olukemi, 15 from Nick Sidorakis and 13 from Keiton Page. Darrell Williams had a team-high nine rebounds. Houston Baptist got 24 points from Andrew Gonzalez and 22 from Miles Dixon. The Cowboys outscored the Huskies, 38-4, in the paint and forced the Huskies into 23 turnovers. Williams had six of Oklahoma State's 18 offensive rebounds. Oklahoma State led 41-28 at halftime and pushed the margin to 20 with just over 14 minutes remaining. A Dixon 3-pointer and a field goal drew the visitors to within nine but a Sidorakis 3 quickly pushed the lead back to 80-68 and Oklahoma State coasted the rest of the way.
